headline: 3 Insurance Stocks We’re Skeptical Of
summary: Insurance firms play a critical role in the financial system, offering everything from property coverage to life insurance and specialized risk solutions. But worries about an economic slowdown and potential claims deterioration have kept sentiment in check, and over the past six months, the industry’s 2.5% return has trailed the S&P 500 by 22.2 percentage points.
